    "### 6.2 Conceptual example: *ultra-processed foods and road accidents*\n",
    "\n",
    "Suppose a cohort analysis found that higher ultra-processed food (UPF) intake was associated with a higher risk of road accidents. This would be biologically implausible. Such a finding would immediately raise concerns about:\n",
    "\n",
    "- confounding by socioeconomic position,\n",
    "- differences in urban versus rural environments,\n",
    "- general health status or risk-taking behaviour.\n",
    "\n",
    "A negative control outcome like this helps us interrogate whether the primary association (for example, UPF and mortality) might be similarly affected by unmeasured confounding.\n"
   ]
  },
