    "## 8. Summary and further reading\n",
    "\n",
    "This workbook outlined key concepts in causal inference:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Observational associations cannot automatically be interpreted as causal.\n",
    "- Bradford Hill considerations remain useful but are not sufficient.\n",
    "- MR exploits genetic instruments but requires strong assumptions.\n",
    "- Negative controls help diagnose confounding and bias.\n",
    "- Counterfactuals define causal effects formally.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Recommended reading\n",
    "\n",
